pull.title: Compat: Simplify bswap_16 implementation
pull.body:
Simplify bswap_16 implementation on platforms which don't already have it defined.
This has no effect on the generated assembly; it just simplifies the source code.

events.body: Does this make any difference in the generated code with your compiler?
utACK. Verified that in GCC 6.3.0 at `-Os`, `-O2` and `-O3` this does not make a difference in the generated code.
